    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a very \"official\" way of putting it. but why do you think there's such a massive push to keep the narrative so simple? if everything was just \"standard science,\" why is there so much secrecy around the telemetry data from those specific early missions? it feels like you're just reciting the brochure. if i were to look specifically at the communication lag logs or the sudden changes in mission objectives during the Apollo era, wouldn't that be a starting point for seeing where the story diverges from the data?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
